1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,780
 So now we're going to solve the problem of a post

2
00:00:02,780 --> 00:00:04,420
 followed by a refresh.

3
00:00:04,420 --> 00:00:06,620
 And we're going to use something we've talked about before.

4
00:00:06,620 --> 00:00:09,200
 We're going to use a redirect, right?

5
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:13,220
 So the basic rule is never send HTML as a result

6
00:00:13,220 --> 00:00:14,380
 at the end of a post request.

7
00:00:14,380 --> 00:00:16,480
 In a sense, if you're gonna return something

8
00:00:16,480 --> 00:00:19,720
 at the end of the post method, return a redirect.

9
00:00:19,720 --> 00:00:21,100
 Don't return HTML.

10
00:00:21,100 --> 00:00:24,020
 Now, we gotta eventually get them some HTML.

11
00:00:24,020 --> 00:00:26,360
 So we redirect to a page that we know,

12
00:00:26,360 --> 00:00:28,780
 and then that will cause a get request,

13
00:00:28,780 --> 00:00:30,600
 and then that page is what we will show.

14
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:34,100
 So the question is, handle post, send a redirect,

15
00:00:34,100 --> 00:00:36,740
 and then redirect to where?

16
00:00:36,740 --> 00:00:38,320
 Now, this is kind of controller, right?

17
00:00:38,320 --> 00:00:40,380
 We talk about model view controller, right?

18
00:00:40,380 --> 00:00:42,460
 Controller is, oh, something happened,

19
00:00:42,460 --> 00:00:44,940
 and I'm gonna move the user's browser from here to here.

20
00:00:44,940 --> 00:00:47,200
 So redirecting, when we're redirecting,

21
00:00:47,200 --> 00:00:49,120
 in a sense, that's a controller function.

22
00:00:49,120 --> 00:00:51,960
 So we often do our redirects from the views.

23
00:00:51,960 --> 00:00:54,500
 Or we're saying here, you're at the end of this view,

24
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:55,700
 you know what, I don't actually want

25
00:00:55,700 --> 00:00:57,060
 to show you a page right now.

26
00:00:57,060 --> 00:00:58,540
 I'm gonna send you to another page

27
00:00:58,540 --> 00:01:00,780
 so that that page you see with a get request.

28
00:01:00,780 --> 00:01:03,740
 Now, we often send ourselves back to the exact same page.

29
00:01:03,740 --> 00:01:05,900
 We take a post on a page,

30
00:01:05,900 --> 00:01:09,340
 and then we redirect right back to the same page.

31
00:01:09,340 --> 00:01:13,660
 So to remember, we got 200 okay, which is a nice page.

32
00:01:13,660 --> 00:01:15,660
 We got 404 not found.

33
00:01:15,660 --> 00:01:18,140
 We saw 403 not authorized before,

34
00:01:18,140 --> 00:01:19,620
 and 302 is found and moved,

35
00:01:19,620 --> 00:01:22,300
 and we're gonna reuse this redirect capability,

36
00:01:22,300 --> 00:01:24,740
 but we're not gonna do a, like, wild redirect

37
00:01:24,740 --> 00:01:26,900
 to a site completely outside of our site.

38
00:01:28,060 --> 00:01:30,940
 So this is a diagram from Wikipedia

39
00:01:30,940 --> 00:01:33,740
 that's talking about the post redirect,

40
00:01:33,740 --> 00:01:35,900
 and on the left side we have the problem

41
00:01:35,900 --> 00:01:38,100
 where the user fills out some kind of a form,

42
00:01:38,100 --> 00:01:40,980
 does a post, changes the data in the server,

43
00:01:40,980 --> 00:01:43,220
 we send back a 200 request,

44
00:01:43,220 --> 00:01:44,860
 says your order was successful,

45
00:01:44,860 --> 00:01:47,100
 and then the user hits the refresh button.

46
00:01:47,100 --> 00:01:49,640
 Now, the key is this only happens if user hits refresh,

47
00:01:49,640 --> 00:01:52,980
 and then the browser asks, are you sure you wanna do that?

48
00:01:52,980 --> 00:01:55,220
 And if you say yes, then it's gonna order twice,

49
00:01:55,220 --> 00:01:57,520
 or deduct the database twice.

50
00:01:57,520 --> 00:02:02,520
 So the solution is for us to have the user fill out the form,

51
00:02:02,520 --> 00:02:05,060
 click a submit, send a post request,

52
00:02:05,060 --> 00:02:08,900
 do the actual transaction, insert an order, or do whatever,

53
00:02:08,900 --> 00:02:11,020
 and then send a 302 redirect,

54
00:02:11,020 --> 00:02:13,560
 and then the browser instantly goes blink, blink, blink,

55
00:02:13,560 --> 00:02:15,960
 there's no, you know, the browser instantly turns this

56
00:02:15,960 --> 00:02:20,540
 into a get, potentially right back to our same page,

57
00:02:20,540 --> 00:02:22,980
 and then we send the page back that says

58
00:02:22,980 --> 00:02:25,060
 your order was successful, or whatever,

59
00:02:25,060 --> 00:02:26,540
 and then if the user refreshes that,

60
00:02:26,540 --> 00:02:30,660
 it just says over and over, your order was successful, okay.

61
00:02:30,660 --> 00:02:33,140
 Now, one of the things we're gonna also show you

62
00:02:33,140 --> 00:02:35,780
 when we do this is that we might actually have

63
00:02:35,780 --> 00:02:38,660
 some kind of a message in that moment of post,

64
00:02:38,660 --> 00:02:40,340
 'cause that's where we got the post data,

65
00:02:40,340 --> 00:02:44,180
 and then we've gotta pass that to the next request,

66
00:02:44,180 --> 00:02:45,940
 and we're gonna use the session to do that,

67
00:02:45,940 --> 00:02:47,440
 and then the message can come out.

68
00:02:47,440 --> 00:02:49,780
 So this whole your order was successful,

69
00:02:49,780 --> 00:02:52,980
 often it knows the order was successful in the post code,

70
00:02:52,980 --> 00:02:56,020
 so we have to send this to the next request,

71
00:02:56,020 --> 00:03:00,100
 and we use the session to get it from the post request

72
00:03:00,100 --> 00:03:01,660
 to the next get request,

73
00:03:01,660 --> 00:03:04,360
 and that's a technique called flash messages,

74
00:03:04,360 --> 00:03:06,780
 and I'll show a simple way of doing that,

75
00:03:06,780 --> 00:03:09,380
 and then later we'll show a more complex way

76
00:03:09,380 --> 00:03:11,620
 to do this Django style.

77
00:03:11,620 --> 00:03:15,180
 Okay, so here we go.

78
00:03:15,180 --> 00:03:18,820
 This is actually the nice way to do this, right?

79
00:03:18,820 --> 00:03:22,680
 So when we first go to the page,

80
00:03:22,680 --> 00:03:24,780
 we're gonna go do a get request.

81
00:03:24,780 --> 00:03:27,460
 We're going to see if there's a message,

82
00:03:27,460 --> 00:03:29,140
 that's that incoming message,

83
00:03:29,140 --> 00:03:31,020
 but it's the first time, so there is no message,

84
00:03:31,020 --> 00:03:33,020
 we'll talk about that in a second.

85
00:03:33,020 --> 00:03:34,980
 If there is a message, once we've got it,

86
00:03:34,980 --> 00:03:37,620
 we're gonna delete it from the session,

87
00:03:37,620 --> 00:03:41,380
 and then we're just going to send the guest.html

88
00:03:41,380 --> 00:03:44,860
 with the message, but the first time to message is false,

89
00:03:44,860 --> 00:03:47,260
 so you'll see no message, right?

90
00:03:47,260 --> 00:03:49,220
 So the first time through in a get request,

91
00:03:49,220 --> 00:03:52,580
 it runs this template, there is no message,

92
00:03:52,580 --> 00:03:54,260
 and then the CSRF token is there,

93
00:03:54,260 --> 00:03:57,960
 and so we get to see that as our get request, okay?

94
00:03:57,960 --> 00:04:00,820
 So that is the get request,

95
00:04:00,820 --> 00:04:03,620
 so we then put in our guest,

96
00:04:03,620 --> 00:04:05,300
 and then we press the submit button.

97
00:04:05,300 --> 00:04:07,260
 That gathers all that data up

98
00:04:07,260 --> 00:04:10,240
 and sends a post to the browser.

99
00:04:10,240 --> 00:04:15,580
 And so that post will end up, after CSRF checking,

100
00:04:15,580 --> 00:04:17,960
 will come here, because it's a post.

101
00:04:17,960 --> 00:04:21,160
 And so what we're going to do

102
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:23,740
 is we're going to grab the guest,

103
00:04:23,740 --> 00:04:26,420
 which now is coming from the post data,

104
00:04:26,420 --> 00:04:29,060
 we're gonna check it, and message is just a message

105
00:04:29,060 --> 00:04:31,020
 of too high, too low, et cetera,

106
00:04:31,020 --> 00:04:32,520
 and now instead of rendering,

107
00:04:32,520 --> 00:04:35,100
 which is what we did before we rendered right here,

108
00:04:35,100 --> 00:04:38,340
 we're actually just gonna set that into the session

109
00:04:38,340 --> 00:04:40,440
 under message, we're gonna store it,

110
00:04:40,440 --> 00:04:42,060
 and then we're gonna send a redirect,

111
00:04:42,060 --> 00:04:45,780
 and we're gonna send a redirect to request.path,

112
00:04:45,780 --> 00:04:47,780
 which means that we're actually telling the browser

113
00:04:47,780 --> 00:04:50,060
 to do a get request right back to us,

114
00:04:50,060 --> 00:04:51,740
 which means it's gonna come in here,

115
00:04:51,740 --> 00:04:53,180
 then it's gonna read the message,

116
00:04:53,180 --> 00:04:56,020
 and then the message is gonna come out here.

117
00:04:56,020 --> 00:04:57,180
 Okay?

118
00:04:57,180 --> 00:04:58,660
 So that's how the post happens.

119
00:04:58,660 --> 00:05:00,060
 Let's go through that again.

120
00:05:00,060 --> 00:05:04,620
 We get the post, we grab the guest, we check the guest,

121
00:05:04,620 --> 00:05:08,300
 and we store our response to the guest in the session,

122
00:05:08,300 --> 00:05:10,540
 and then we redirect back to ourselves,

123
00:05:10,540 --> 00:05:11,960
 which comes into the get,

124
00:05:11,960 --> 00:05:14,140
 we pull the message out of the session,

125
00:05:14,140 --> 00:05:16,100
 we delete the message from the session,

126
00:05:16,100 --> 00:05:18,020
 and then we actually render the page.

127
00:05:18,020 --> 00:05:19,900
 So you get the original get request,

128
00:05:19,900 --> 00:05:23,800
 you type in your guest, hit the submit button,

129
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:26,260
 went to the URL awesome,

130
00:05:26,260 --> 00:05:30,480
 but it came back with a 302, not with a 200,

131
00:05:30,480 --> 00:05:33,700
 and with a location that says go back to get post awesome.

132
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:35,860
 So that's the same URL that we posted to,

133
00:05:35,860 --> 00:05:37,580
 we posted to the URL.

134
00:05:37,580 --> 00:05:40,620
 And if we look underneath the response,

135
00:05:40,620 --> 00:05:43,060
 we'll find that that's empty, okay?

136
00:05:43,060 --> 00:05:46,900
 So on the post request, there is nothing in the response,

137
00:05:46,900 --> 00:05:49,440
 there is no page, because what we're seeing here

138
00:05:49,440 --> 00:05:52,340
 is the result of this get request, okay?

139
00:05:52,340 --> 00:05:56,020
 So what happens is is that the browser sees the 302,

140
00:05:56,020 --> 00:05:58,540
 sees the location, and immediately turns around

141
00:05:58,540 --> 00:05:59,900
 and does a get request.

142
00:05:59,900 --> 00:06:03,660
 And then that get request has this page,

143
00:06:03,660 --> 00:06:05,100
 and then it's gonna get a favicon,

144
00:06:05,100 --> 00:06:07,500
 which is just another get request.

145
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:09,020
 And so this is the get after the redirect,

146
00:06:09,020 --> 00:06:11,460
 and we can see the data that's associated with it,

147
00:06:11,460 --> 00:06:14,500
 and it's got, this one actually has a real response,

148
00:06:14,500 --> 00:06:17,100
 it's a real 200, and then we have the real page,

149
00:06:17,100 --> 00:06:19,500
 and that renders it, and then it grabs the favicon

150
00:06:19,500 --> 00:06:23,540
 just so that it can put a nice cute little favicon up there.

151
00:06:23,540 --> 00:06:27,740
 Now, if we hit refresh, so we sit on this page,

152
00:06:27,740 --> 00:06:31,360
 and we hit the refresh, then what'll happen

153
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:34,260
 is it'll rerun the most recent thing,

154
00:06:34,260 --> 00:06:37,020
 and the most recent thing that we got was this get request,

155
00:06:37,020 --> 00:06:39,020
 which means it does another get request.

156
00:06:39,020 --> 00:06:40,900
 Whereas before, it was redoing the post request,

157
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:42,340
 and that's why it was complaining.

158
00:06:42,340 --> 00:06:44,860
 So you get no message, you get no problem,

159
00:06:44,860 --> 00:06:46,220
 you get absolutely nothing.

160
00:06:46,220 --> 00:06:48,500
 So it's actually really quite pretty.

161
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:51,280
 So here is the pretty little way of doing it.

162
00:06:51,280 --> 00:06:55,260
 And the simple rule is, the first rule is,

163
00:06:55,260 --> 00:06:59,020
 at the bottom of a post method, you should be redirecting.

164
00:06:59,020 --> 00:07:02,260
 If you're sending a screen back at the bottom

165
00:07:02,260 --> 00:07:04,920
 of a post message after the data's been handled,

166
00:07:04,920 --> 00:07:06,580
 then it's a mistake.

167
00:07:06,580 --> 00:07:09,500
 So the steps are we go to the page, we do a get request,

168
00:07:09,500 --> 00:07:11,460
 there is no message, so we get sort of the page

169
00:07:11,460 --> 00:07:13,980
 with no message, then we do a post request,

170
00:07:13,980 --> 00:07:16,780
 the post request comes in, we check the guest,

171
00:07:16,780 --> 00:07:19,460
 we put the message in the session, and then we redirect,

172
00:07:19,460 --> 00:07:21,620
 and then it comes back to a second get,

173
00:07:21,620 --> 00:07:23,780
 pulls the message out of the session,

174
00:07:23,780 --> 00:07:25,920
 deletes the message from the session,

175
00:07:25,920 --> 00:07:28,860
 and then renders it with the message and everything.

176
00:07:28,860 --> 00:07:33,100
 And that's called flash message, flash message pattern,

177
00:07:33,100 --> 00:07:36,000
 in particular because we're deleting it

178
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:37,660
 after we've shown it to the user.

179
00:07:37,660 --> 00:07:42,500
 So next we're gonna switch to how Django actually

180
00:07:42,500 --> 00:07:46,340
 has forms.py and makes it easy to construct forms,

181
00:07:46,340 --> 00:07:48,820
 so we're not gonna be writing a bunch of input tags,

182
00:07:48,820 --> 00:07:51,740
 or option tags, or select tags.

183
00:07:51,740 --> 00:07:53,860
 Django makes this a lot easier for us.

184
00:07:53,860 --> 00:07:56,440
 (upbeat music)

